Introduction

WANNA.B was a five-member girl group under Zenith Media Contents. It is assumed that the group quietly disbanded in late 2019. The final lineup consisted of Sejin, Roeun, Lina, Ami and Eunsom.

Originally set to debut as a four-piece, WANNA.B released a pre-debut single titled "My Type" on November 17, 2014. Prior to the group's official debut in 2015, members Saebom and J.Bin left the lineup and were replaced by Siyoung and Sejin. Yoonseul also left the group before debut, and with her departure came the introduction of three additional members: Seoyoon (formerly of Luluz), Eunsom (formerly of Luluz and BADKIZ), and Ami (formerly of NEP). WANNA.B officially debuted on July 20, 2015, with the single "Attention." In the same year, they made their first comeback with "Hands Up" on November 10.

On April 6, 2016, Zenith Media Contents announced Seoyoon's departure from WANNA.B and the addition of two new members, Lina and Roeun. Now promoting as a seven-member group, WANNA.B released "Why?" on June 26, 2016. In November 2016, members Jiwoo and Siyoung left the group. It would be nearly three years before WANNA.B had another comeback on February 20, 2019, with "Leggo."

Sometime in 2019, Sejin removed any mention of the group from her Instagram account and was unfollowed by the group's official account. All the remaining members would follow suit in late 2019 and any mention of WANNA.B was removed from the official Zenith Media Contents website, suggesting that the group had quietly disbanded.
